== a standalone assignment is silent, the read prints the value:
5
10
== a formula binds before its inputs and recomputes lazily:
12
40
== an assignment is an expression mid-line, returning its value:
6
5
== a == comparison is not an assignment:
1
0
== an unset variable is a located capitalized error, not a silent zero:
shit: 1:1: error: The variable 'nope' is not set.
     1 |  nope
       |  ^~~~ here.
== a set but empty variable reads zero, only an unset name is an error:
0
== an empty assignment is rejected rather than binding an empty value:
shit: 1:1: error: Assignment to 'z' needs a value.
     1 |  z =
       |  ^~ here.
== a division by zero is a located capitalized error:
shit: 1:6: error: Division by zero.
     1 |  1 / 0
       |       ^~ here.
note: The right operand evaluated to 0.
== an unset name inside a stored formula errors when the formula reads:
shit: error: The variable 'base' is not set.
